An Act amending death and disability compensation for members of the armed forces and the
organized militia of the Commonwealth.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 88 of chapter 33 of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022
2 Official Edition, is hereby amended in subsection (a) by striking out the words “An officer or
3 enlisted person of the Massachusetts organized militia” and inserting in place thereof the
4 following words:- “Members of the armed forces of the Commonwealth of Massachusetts and
5 Massachusetts organized militia”.
6 SECTION 2. Said section 88 subsection (a), as so appearing, is further amended by
7 striking out the words “a board” in line 4 and inserting in place thereof the following words:-
8 “The Death Gratuity Board (the “Board”)”.
9 SECTION 3. Said section 88 subsection (b), as so appearing, is further amended by
10 adding in place thereof the following:- “Members of the armed forces of the Commonwealth of
11 Massachusetts and Massachusetts organized militia who, while performing any duty lawfully
