12 ordered under this chapter without willful neglect on the part of the person, dies, shall, receive
13 compensation as described by a Board appointed under section 90 for a determination of death
14 gratuity benefits as described in paragraph (c) below. The Board shall consider death or injury
15 arising from present or past qualified duty status on behalf of the Commonwealth of
16 Massachusetts or United States of America. Qualified Duty Status is defined as State Active
17 Duty and service pursuant to orders under Titles 10 and 32 of the US Code.
18 SECTION 4. Said section 88 subsection (b), as so appearing, is further amended by
19 striking out the letter “(b)” and inserting in place thereof the following:- “(c)”.
20 SECTION 5. Said section 88 updated subsection (c), as so appearing, is further amended
21 by striking out the following words:- “If the death of a member of the Massachusetts organized
22 militia results from injury, sickness or disease received while in the line of duty, pursuant to
23 orders under titles 10 and 32 of the United States Code or this chapter and the injury, sickness or
24 disease resulting in the death”, and inserting in place thereof the following words:- “If the death
25 results from injury, sickness, or disease received while in the line of duty, pursuant to orders”.
26 SECTION 6. Said section 88 subsection (c), as so appearing, is further amended by
27 striking out the letter “(c)” and inserting in place thereof the following:- “(d)”.
28 SECTION 7. Said section 88 updated subsection (d), as so appearing, is further amended
29 by striking out the letter “(b)” in line 15 and inserting in place thereof the following:- “(c)”.
30 SECTION 8. Said section 88 updated subsection (d), as so appearing, is further amended
31 by striking out the words “a member of the Massachusetts organized militia”, and inserting in
32 place thereof the following words:- “a member of the armed forces of the Commonwealth of
33 Massachusetts and / or Massachusetts organized militia”.
